rsial interrogation techniques today. Readers will be able to make informed judgements about whether, on the basis of the results of these cases, interrogation techniques that might be described as torture can be justified.This book will be of particular interest to security professionals, academics and members of the public interested in the torture debate, intelligence, the military, counter-insurgency, counter-terrorism, foreign policy and law enforcement.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aIntelligence servicezGreat Britain. 0aMilitary interrogationzGreat Britain. 0aQuestioningzGreat Britain. 0aTorturezGreat Britain. 4aSecurity, Conflict & Peace 2018. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Intelligence & Espionage.2bisacsh  aAden.  aCounter-Insurgency.  aCounter-Terrorism.  aIntelligence.  aInterrogation.  aIraq.  aNorthern Ireland.  aPolicy.  aSecurity.  aTorture.1 aNewbery, Samantha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2015 eBook-Packagez978311128311140uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978071909835240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780719098352423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780719098352/original  a978-3-11-128311-1  Manchester University Press 2015 eBook-Packageb2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles